                            <comment id="16199905" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 11 Oct 2017 07:19:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thomas, you closed the PR so is there another PR coming or did the PR not work etc?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16199909" author="tdiesler" created="Wed, 11 Oct 2017 07:29:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The PR is working, but I haven&apos;t decided yet whether the correct classloader to use should be that of the Optaplaner component, the Kie API or even that of the user deployment. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Kie caches classloaders that are associated with an arbitrary thread. This is of course highly problematic in a modular environment, where the same instance of Kie may be used by multiple modules and even multiple deployments.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Only if that what is cached is part of some static configuration (i.e. independent of deployment content) it can (reluctantly) be done at all. &lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;ll revisit this at my leisure and for now agree with you, that it is not critical.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
